properties.Title: Frost Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Clearing skies with temperatures falling to zero, or colder in low lying areas, will give frost to parts of northern and western New Brunswick early Friday morning. ### Frost advisories are issued when temperatures are expected to reach the freezing mark during the growing season, leading to potential damage and destruction to plants and crops. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NBstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NBStorm.
Expires: 2019-05-17T17:33:08-00:00

properties.Title: Wind Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Arctic high pressure over the NWT combined with low pressure over the Yukon is driving very strong winds across the Richardson Mountains. Easterly winds of 80 km/h gusting to 100 will continue to impact the northern Dempster Highway today before gradually ease this evening. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather in British Columbia or Yukon, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or YTstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm or #YTStorm.
Expires: 2019-05-18T03:23:21-00:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Environment Canada, 2019-05-17T11:24:21-00:00, urn:oid:2.49.0.1.124.0489286212.2019
Area: Dempster
properties.Author: Environment Canada

properties.Title: Frost Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Frost may damage some crops in frost-prone areas. Temperatures dropping to near zero in low lying areas, combined with clearing skies overnight, will give conditions for patchy frost early Friday morning. ### Frost advisories are issued when temperatures are expected to reach the freezing mark during the growing season, leading to potential damage and destruction to plants and crops. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NSstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NSStorm.
